      "content": "Even if you felt fine before, that doesn't mean it's safe for your current pregnancy, so you must treat it as a serious precaution. Using antibiotics without a doctor's specific approval during pregnancy is risky because of potential fetal side effects. Instead of medication, try a hot compress over your sinuses to help loosen things up while you wait for Monday. For severe pain, some pregnancy-safe pain relievers might be an option, but only if you confirm it with a pharmacist.",
